com.googlecode.slotted.client

Class HistoryMapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.googlecode.slotted.client.HistoryMapper
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AutoHistoryMapper

    public abstract class HistoryMapper
extends java.lang.Object
    HistoryMapper is an abstract base class that manages generation and parsing of History Tokens. This class is extended by every implementation of Slotted and defines which SlottedPlaces need URL management.

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      HistoryMapper()
      Default constructor which adds itself as a History listener and calls init() on the base class to register all SlottedPlaces.

      • registerPlace

        public void registerPlace(java.lang.Class<? extends SlottedPlace> placeClass)
        Registers the passed SlottedPlace be handled in generating and parsing History tokens. The SlottedPlace's simple class name will be used in the HistoryToken. If the name ends with "Place", that will be stripped off. (i.e. "HomePlace" will appear as "Home" in the token)
        Parameters:
        placeClass - The Class of the place to be managed. The Place must have a default constructor, but it may be private.
        See Also:
        registerPlace(SlottedPlace, String)

      • registerPlace

        public void registerPlace(java.lang.Class<? extends SlottedPlace> placeClass,
                 com.google.gwt.place.shared.PlaceTokenizer<? extends SlottedPlace> tokenizer)
        Same as registerPlace(SlottedPlace), but allows for the Place to create token with parameters specific to the Place. This allows parameters to be Place specific to prevent name collisions.
        Parameters:
        placeClass - The Class of the place to be managed. The Place must have a default constructor, but it may be private.
        tokenizer - That handles the creation of the token and parsing the token into a Place.

      • registerPlace

        public void registerPlace(java.lang.Class<? extends SlottedPlace> placeClass,
                 java.lang.String name)
        Same as registerPlace(SlottedPlace), but allows Places URL token to be overridden, instead of using the simple class name.
        Parameters:
        placeClass - The Class of the place to be managed. The Place must have a default constructor, but it may be private.
        name - The new URL token to display in the History token, must be URL safe.

      • registerPlace

        public void registerPlace(java.lang.Class<? extends SlottedPlace> placeClass,
                 java.lang.String name,
                 com.google.gwt.place.shared.PlaceTokenizer<? extends SlottedPlace> tokenizer)
        Same as registerPlace(SlottedPlace), but allows for overridden name, and parameter tokens.
        Parameters:
        placeClass - The Class of the place to be managed. The Place must have a default constructor, but it may be private.
        name - The new URL token to display in the History token, must be URL safe.
        tokenizer - That handles the creation of the token and parsing the token into a Place.
        See Also:
        registerPlace(Class, PlaceTokenizer), registerPlace(Class, String)
